Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into evenly-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} top down through the middle (but not all the way through).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Add the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{2%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, pop the meatballs onto a large baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the meatballs have 2-3 mins left, pop the buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Move the wedges to the bottom shelf of your oven.

Once the meatballs are cooked, wipe the tray clean and pop the warmed buns on. Spread each with the @burger sauce{30%g}, then share the meatballs between the buns and top with the cheese.

Bake on the top shelf until the cheese is melted and bubbly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, transfer the meatball subs to your plates and serve the wedges alongside.

Finish with a handful of @wild rocket{20%g} on the side and spoon the caramelised onions on top of the meatball subs to finish.

Enjoy!